# Upstream CVEs

# gRPC-Go: Authorization bypass due to improper HTTP/2 path validation in grpc/authz middleware
# chaos-runner uses gRPC only as an OTLP tracing client (otlptracegrpc exporter); it never
# serves gRPC nor uses the authz interceptor
CVE-2026-33186

# OpenTelemetry Go SDK: Arbitrary code execution via PATH hijacking
# PATH hijacking requires planting a malicious binary in $PATH, which is not feasible inside
# a read-only container filesystem; chaos-runner is also a short-lived Kubernetes job
CVE-2026-24051

# opentelemetry-go: BSD kenv command not using absolute path enables PATH hijacking
# BSD-specific attack vector (kenv is a FreeBSD utility); not applicable on Linux containers
CVE-2026-39883

# golang.org/x/oauth2/jws: Unexpected memory consumption during token parsing
# Not in use as shown by govulncheck
CVE-2025-22868
